<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,395,1870,1896]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Coeliccia pyriformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laidlaw" box="[403,578,1871,1897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" refString="Laidlaw, F. F. (1932) A revision of the genus Coeliccia (Order Odonata). Records of the Indian Museum, 34, 7 - 42, 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1932">
Laidlaw, 
<number box="[519,578,1871,1897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" value="1932.0">1932</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1941,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<collectingCountry box="[151,182,1942,1966]" name="American Samoa" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">As</collectingCountry>
pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dow" box="[358,507,1942,1966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" refString="Dow, R. A. (2011 a) Coeliccia pyriformis. In: IUCN 2012. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2012.2. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / details / 167436 / 0 (accessed 11 April 2013)" type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="a">
Dow (
<number box="[427,486,1942,1966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
, the original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[816,1047,1941,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Platycnemididae" genus="Coeliccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[816,1047,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Coeliccia pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laidlaw" box="[1088,1261,1941,1966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" refString="Laidlaw, F. F. (1932) A revision of the genus Coeliccia (Order Odonata). Records of the Indian Museum, 34, 7 - 42, 3 pls." type="journal article" year="1932">
Laidlaw (
<number box="[1195,1253,1942,1966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" value="1932.0">1932</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
lacks drawings as well as a sufficiently detailed description. Here, we redescribe the 
<typeStatus box="[968,1066,1977,2002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">holotype</typeStatus>
and discuss inaccuracies in the original description. The potential synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[693,842,2014,2038]" class="Insecta" family="Platycnemididae" genus="Coeliccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[693,842,2014,2038]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">C. pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Asahina, 1997" authorityName="Asahina" authorityYear="1997" box="[897,1154,2013,2038]" class="Insecta" family="Platycnemididae" genus="Coeliccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acco">
<emphasis box="[897,982,2014,2037]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">C. acco</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina" box="[989,1154,2013,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" refString="Asahina, S. (1997) Records of the northernVietnamese Odonata taken by the expedition members from the National Science Museum, Tokyo, 5: Coenagrionidae, Protoneuridae, Platycnemididae. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo (A), 23, 17 - 34." type="journal article" year="1997">
Asahina, 
<number box="[1095,1154,2014,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is discussed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
